<p>Historically, western Tamil Nadu’s towns have seen election-season seizures that became reference points in campaign speeches—sometimes fairly, sometimes as exaggeration. March 15’s operations unfolded in that echo chamber: every bundle of currency stopped for verification could be spun into partisan narrative unless departments released careful, aggregate statistics rather than anecdotal leaks.</p>

