<p>With polling day approaching, more drills—flag marches, vehicle checks, and spot raids—may follow intelligence flows. Police appealed to citizens to carry valid ID, avoid moving large cash without bills, and report suspicious stocking of liquor or goods. The district control room and election helplines remain active conduits for verified complaints.</p>

<p>For Coimbatore, March 15 was one tile in a mosaic: polling personnel training, vulnerable booth mapping, and surveillance on inducement networks all run concurrently. The measure of success will not be headlines alone but whether voters walk to booths without fear—and whether the innocent never dread a knock.</p>

