<h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>

<h3>What is a cordon and search operation?</h3>
<p>Police seal an area temporarily, restrict entry and exit, and search premises or persons based on legal authority and intelligence, aiming to recover contraband or verify identities.</p>

<h3>Do I have to allow officers inside my home?</h3>
<p>Cooperation is expected when police act under lawful authority; ask for identification, note names and station details, and seek legal help if you believe procedures were violated.</p>

<h3>Was March 15 only about elections?</h3>
